# System Monitor - Deployment & Distribution Guide

This guide explains how to package your project so users only need **ONE file** ([start-universal.sh](file:///c:/Users/DELL/Desktop/system-monitor-project-Batch/start-universal.sh)) to run it.

## Part 1: Developer Guide (Preparation)

### 1. Push Code to GitHub
**CRITICAL:** You must push the updated [start-universal.sh](file:///c:/Users/DELL/Desktop/system-monitor-project-Batch/start-universal.sh) to your GitHub repository so users can download it.

```bash
git add start-universal.sh
git commit -m "Update startup script with auto-generated config"
git push origin main
```

### 2. Push Image to Docker Hub
Upload the Dashboard container so the script can pull it.

```bash
# 1. Login
docker login

# 2. Tag (Using your username)
docker tag system-monitor:latest sharawey74/system-monitor:latest

# 3. Push
docker push sharawey74/system-monitor:latest
```

